reviews.review_text: Been arriving in Vancouver by train and was looking to get something to eat nearby, trying to push my luggage on the way. Now the reviews of this small eatery point are being favorable, favorable of the PB and Bacon Burger too, so I tried. Like they all say, its an absolute mess, with no ending. Too much juicy meat, too much of the crispiest bacons I ever had, too much of the peanut butter, not even thinking to try to stay between the patties. Overall it wasnt the best burger I ever had, but a very good one. The poutine on the other hand really kicked in. Ive never tried it that way, the chaos of flavor was a special treatment for my tounge, in a great way. The girls working here are very kind and also handling situations with a I believe its real smile. Nothing to complain here. If I ever come back to Vancouver again, this will be on my bucket list for sure. And next time Im gonna ask for some wet tissues first, before I have to see my fingers being soaked up in PB again.
Truly to dine for, the food has been delicious each and every time. The atmosphere and staff are so friendly and personable. I will be back again for sure.
Vancouver best restaurants!!!! I moved to Calgary, but I couldnt forget this place and came back on this Vancouver trip. Service, taste !!!!!! Everything in this place is perfect
The best burger and fries in Vancouver area. All staffs are really kind and polite. I want to go there everyday.

The outstanding quality of the burger will recalibrate your burger standards. It even hurts your heart not to be able to have this cafe near your workplace, to come down for an exceptional taste everyday. When you are tired of the franchise competition bragging about its originality, please give this jam a try, and you will know what is truly original.

Had the pleasure of trying out TO DINE FOR Eatery.  Had the turkey club, chicken rice soup, B.E.LT.,  fries, and the spaghetti to go. The spaghetti was so good, reminded me on my moms home cooking.  The turkey club and BELT were made with fresh ingredients. A must try when you are in the terminal area.  Decor was on point with the diner.  They are having gelato as well coming soon!!! Awesome service and friendly atmosphere Looking forward to my next visit!

Honestly, my new favorite diner and burger joint. My family and our friends absolutely love it. The diner is open for dine-in now. Their specialty burgers are the highlight. However, their soups, fries and drinks are also really nice. The staff were very friendly and attentive. Plexiglass is installed and covid procedures well-followed. I felt welcomed and safe and enjoyed an awesome lunch. Its local and family-owned. The area was very clean. Also tried their spaghetti and curry on another occassion -- both are also quite nice when you are craving for something different. I cant wait to go back to try the entire menu.
One of the most flavorful burgers Ive ever eaten, was tangy and juicy and beefy, really really good food! I got the mushroom lovers burger
All the ingredients were fresh and delicious, and above all, the staff were so friendly!!
Best real burger in town and the fries too!

Really, this is my new favourite burger and diner place. Everyone in my family and our friends adores it. Diners can now eat in at the diner. The star is their speciality burgers. However, they also have some really good soups, fries, and drinks. The personnel was really helpful and kind. Installation of Plexiglass and careful adherence to COVID procedures. I had a great lunch and felt welcomed and protected. Local and family-run business. It was really clean there.
Great place for burgers and sandwhiches! The burger is so flavorful and filling. It ll be my go to lunch place.
Excellent burgers and service was great. All the servers are very friendly.

I ordered the grilled chicken and fries. Both were delicious. Lived up to the expectation! (Sign outside says best burger). Portion was generous. The lady on the front was really nice. Excellent customer service!

Decided to put their  best burger in town  sign to the test. They were not lying, this place really serves up one of the best burgers in Vancouver! Huge portions, juice burgers, hot crispy fries. Service was excellent. Definitely give this place a try!
LOVE THIS PLACE!!!!  The team members especially the young lady who serves us is suuuper sweet and friendly!!  The food is amazing as well!!  Thanks again for being awesome!!!
One of the best loaded burgers Ive ever had...I can go there everyday :) thanks a ton guys and keep it up :)

Amazing food and great burgers! Love their homemade muffins and pastries! So rich in flavour plus my favourite breakfast item is their eggs Bennie yummm! Their fries are good too! And the grilled chicken burger is a must try! Plus nice and friendly service :)
Really great food and service! Highly recommend :)

Literally the best burger in town. We ordered the mushroom burger as takeout and unfortunately had to eat it an hour after we got it. But regardless of it being cold, it was delicious. Cant imagine how much better it would be served hot. The best!

The sign outside proclaiming  best burger in town  was so outrageous, it had served as joking point with my friends for over a year. It was even easier to laugh at because the restaurant was closed during the early pandemic and in sort of a weird location. However, after finally trying one of their burgers, the sign is not that funny anymore. It was a really good burger. If it s not the best burger in town, it s at least the second best burger in town. Portion sizes are enormous, I mean ENORMOUS.

Great Burgers! ~ you can taste the quality ingredients that they use for the burgers.. .. I found the price reasonable for such a tasty burger - My opinion it is WAY better than that any chain burger... We came in from Maple Ridge to the Swap Meet and I googled a good burger place close by...My whole family loved their meals !!!  -   We will definitely come back.!!! Great Burger Great service!

The food is absolutely delicious. I never knew about this place but my friend suggested we go here and I had a fantastic experience. Ever since then.. Ive been here over 10 times now. The burgers are so good. The owners are so friendly, generous and kind!! I will be back!!

Ive had the bacon avocado sandwich here at least 10 times and *every* time the avocado is perfect ripeness. I dont know what kind of magic they do here but this is consistently the best sandwich Ive had in the city.

Such a good burger place! Super friendly staff. I wish it was open later, it seems to be better known for its lunch then dinner. Dont be afraid to try something different. I had the peanut butter bacon burger and it was amazing.
This place has amazing food, and big portions! Their burgers were fresh, homemade and to die for! ;) I cant wait to try more of their menu, I will be a repeat visitor for sure!

Seriously the BEST burger in town! My favorite is the flaming hot burger and my husband loves the blackstone Benny. Ingredients are always so fresh and everything is delicious! Couldn t recommend this place more!
Burgers were DELICIOUS. Jane at the front counter is a delight. A must go restaurant in Vancouver. My girlfriend agrees and shes very picky. PERIODT.

The sign outside says best burgers in the city and its not far off. Had the PBB burger and the peanut butter sauce was super rich with the crunchiest bacon Ive even had in a burger. Dont miss out if youre in the area.

My favourite place to go eat lunch near work. Their burgers are fantastic (though they do take some time, like most good things), and I especially enjoy their Southeast Asian style beef curry. Add an extra egg on top if youre feeling lucky

My husband and I love their burgers. Even now with a newborn we still make our way there, thats how good the burgers are :). I also tried the bibimbop tonight, excellent!  We keep saying its amomg the best burgers in Vancouver, if not outright the best. Keep up the good work!

A hidden gem, my fav place burgers in Vancouver!!!! Highly recommend the Crying Chicken burger, peanut butter bacon burger and house baked banana blue-berry muffins. So happy theyre open during the pandemic, the owner mentioned that theyre looking into Doordash as well!

If you would like a burger experience then come and try one here. Amazing tasting burger with large serving of frys. You would never know it from the outside but this is a gem of a burger place to find. The price does seem higher than usual but after eating I can guarantee satisfaction. Delish!! Vegetarian burgers also.
The Hot TDF is by far the best burger Ive ever eaten in my life.  The spicy sauce tastes amazing and is not overly hot.  The service here is also very good.

They served me the best bacon cheeseburger Ive ever had. I fully understand why they were awarded *vancouvers best burger 2014. Along with my burger I had poutine which was untraditional but amazing nonetheless. Definitely recommend as I will be going back many many times.

Fantastic  food, from burger to coffee ! they have chosen to use real good food for doing their hamburgers (organic, local), and it is pricy because it is delicious and charming. For who wants to compare to usual fast-foods, you are just so wrong. this is a restaurant with delicious burger, real plates, real drinks, real service.
I absolutely love this place!!! Amazing burgers, great service and really nice place to dine at. I keep coming back for the burgers, though everything in the menu looks really good. Thank you!(:

The food and coffee is excellent, generous portions and fair prices. The service was fast and friendly. I highly recommended checking this spot out. Cant wait to come back again and have their sweety brown chicken :)

Eaten here 5 times or so now at lunch time. highly recommended.  Always seems busy but i never have waited for a table. food is spot on, the nickname our company gives to this place is Best Burger simply because its true!
The TDF burger is the best burger Ive ever had in my life.  Everything was so fresh and had so much flavour.  Great service too.  My new favourite place to eat.
Small mom & pop restaurant but big on quality and flavour Everything is handmade here, and owner puts a lot of effort in preparing all ingredients They also sell Marios Gelati
Exceptional service and great food! Most of the food is made in house and the service staff were incredible! Will definitely come back.
Best burger in town, the owners are wonderful people.  The food is spectacular.
Service was awesome and the burgers were delicious. Prices might seem steep but they are better than veras or splitz grill for sure and in the same ball park.
Delicious food and very courteous staff. Went specifically for the PB Burger and was not disappointed. Just wish the hours were a little more extensive.
I tried their Flame Burger with a side of (untraditional) poutine.  So hot.  So spicy.  Sooooooo good! Wonderful friendly service too.  Will definitely be back for more.
When I first saw the best burger in town sign I was skeptical to say the least. But it really is an amazing burger!
Best burger eatery in Vancouver! Fantastic food, kind staff. Definitely a 5-star restaurant for sure.
One of the greatest peppermint mochas I had
Amazing place, best burgers ever and the loveliest family run business in Vancouver!  dont miss out on this place!
Friendly staff, great food and great coffee :) I love coming here!!!!
Fantastic burgers. If youre lucky, you might also get a portion of the house bibimbap. Delicious
Always a solid burger. Great hand cut fries. And friendly warm staff
Food: 10/10 Customer Service: 10/10 Location: 10/10 Cant recommend this place enough! Burgers and curry are my favs!
The Kimchi burger is worth the price of admission alone. And those fries are oh so perfectly crisp!
Really big portions! Got a burger and fries for lunch, everything was delicious. Would definitely go back.
Super friendly and welcoming staff. I really enjoy their Sweetie Brown Chicken and their Korean Rice bowl. :)
Awesome burgers perfect fries and super service and oh ya.. great coffee!
Amazing burgers. Went specifically for the PB and bacon burger which did not disappoint.
I really enjoy the food and the place. I have been many times and it is great value for money. Parking can be scarce sometimes.
Wow. Burger is to DIE for.. Cafeteria-style restaurant with a phenomenal burger. Reminded me of a Mr Mikes burger in their heyday.
Fantastic burgers for far less money than the mediocre shitburgers at relish or cannibal. Fries are good too
Very good burgers and friendly staff... I go every week or two
I loved it!!! The staff there really were amazing. And the burgers were delicious
One of the best burger places in town!
B.E.L.T. Sandwitch its amazing... French fries as well!! You should definitely try it ... !!  :)
Great handmade burgers, crisp flavorful fries, friendly staff
My all time fav spot for lunch! Excellent food. Good service.
Amazing food! Especially the Burgers are extraordinaire !
My favorite Burger place !!! Everybody should try it.
Burger Nirvana.  Burger Heaven. The Holy Grail of Vancouver Burgers.  You get the idea!
Best BELT! Very friendly too. Wish they had more open hours
Great food. Friendly staff. Nice coffee.
Best burgers in town, always great service
I just had tea and muffin, these items were good
Delicious food. Great customer service!
The Holy Smokes burger is delicious and a must try
Amazing food. And Paleo friendly if you ask.
Nice and colourful restaurant, and the food was great.
Fantastic burgers, highly recommend
Excellent service and food served with a smile!
Good food, nice staff, quick service.
Good place for eating
generous portions, excellent quality !
Awesome Burgers. Especially the crying chicken
Get the Peanut Butter burger, your face will thank you.
Great food great portion great services.
Best burger in town.
Best burgers in Vancouver
If you go, you will see.
Good food and friendly service.
Amazing burger!!
The burgers are amazzzzing
Great burgers!!!!
Excellent chips
Best burgers in Vancouver

This is the best hamburger restaurant in Vancouver that is always delicious. They are friendly and, above all, they seem to have a philosophy about food... I came right away after hearing that they had opened after being closed due to the coronavirus. There are take out and some dine-in options. It looks like it~~ Its really delicious. Especially the spicy burger is the best for Koreans taste~~ Bobs Burger is delicious anytime you eat it~~^^ Be sure to stop by and try it~~ !!
The food was delicious and the staff were friendly and nice. Is the person taking your order friendly, especially the person serving you? They were really kind.
The food here has never disappointed me. The coffee is very fresh The best organic coffee in Vancouver
The first food I ate in Canada, Bulgogi Rice Bowl The first food I ate in Canada is bulgogi over rice.
